<b>Subject:</b> Agreed<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=921" TARGET=_self>Re: TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL</A> (Galford Teveril[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>To tell the truth, the PvP system that is currently being used is pretty damn well thought out. The level handicap prevents mass slaughtering of would be newbie PK's, which in itself helps promote the PvP shard since it's the numbers that Verant will be watching come final. The major aspect of EQ PvP is the importance of levels, it's critical in any fight and even more so in PvP. It's PvP for once instead of PKing, a world of difference between the two ;)

<P>DarkBlight- Changing with the times
<P>&gt; I'm sorry, but you people saying there should be no level limit
<BR>&gt; at all obviously haven't played this game that much. LEVELS MEAN
<BR>&gt; EVERYTHING IN EQ!!!!
<BR>&gt; Galford Teveril of Covetous Crew
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
